.SH Synopsis
   Defined in header <type_traits>
   template< class T >              \fI(since C++11)\fP
   struct is_abstract;

   If T is an abstract class (that is, a class that declares or inherits at least one
   pure virtual function), provides the member constant value equal true. For any other
   type, value is false.

